<P>We compared immunoreactivity for angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) in
pulmonary artery and lung parenchymal tissues (obtained at the time of resection
for lung transplantation) from eight patients with Stage IV primary pulmonary
hypertension (PPH) with the reactivity in similar tissues from eight normal
donors. ACE immunoreactivity was markedly and consistently increased in the
